          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Astrophysical S factor for a-capture on 112Sn in the",
                " p-process energy range"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDGT"
                ],
                "institute": "1USANOT"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " FN Tandem Van de Graaff accelerator",
                " at the University of Notre Dame, USA, in the energy",
                " range 7.59-11.42 MeV"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "112Sn targets were irradiated with an alpha beam in",
                " the energy range starting from 7.59 MeV in energy",
                " steps of 0.5 MeV. The typical current recorded was",
                " between 200 and 250 nA"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The detection system was composed of two Clover",
                " Ge detectors (Clover 1 and Clover 2), each detector",
                " having four HPGe crystals"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Isotopically enriched 112Sn targets in the form of",
                " thin self-supporting foils of 2.2mg/cm2 were used for",
                " the measurements. The highly enriched (99.60 %)",
                " 112Sn targets were prepared at Argonne National",
                " Laboratory via mechanical rolling. The 112Sn foils",
                " were mounted on Ta frames with hole diameters of",
                " 12.5 mm. The target thickness was determined by",
                " Rutherford back scattering (RBS) to be 2.2 +/-",
                " 0.2 mg/cm2 and was verified at the end of the",
                " experiment."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The total error of the measured cross section values",
                " includes two components: statistical error based on",
                " counting statistics of the analyzed gamma-lines",
                " (between 0.2 and 25% depending on the bombarding",
                " energy) and systematical error based on the",
                " errors in the procedural techniques such as the",
                " error in the efficiency measurement (2%), the error",
                " in the beam current integration (2%), and target",
                " thickness (9%). These components were added in",
                " quadrature."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": 0.2,
                "maximum_value": 25.0,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Statistical error"
